h3 Code
h4 Inline code
p.-text Code tags are used to wrap inline snippets of code.
.example.-mb3
  p.-text.-m3
    | This <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> will render as inline code.
  :code(lang="html")
    This <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> will render as inline code.
h4 Code blocks
p.-text Pre tags are used to wrap multiple lines of code.
.example.-mb3
  .code-block.-m3
    pre
      code &lt;p&gt;This code will render as a code block.&lt;/p&gt;
  :code(lang="html")
    <pre>
      <code>&lt;p&gt;This code will render as a code block.&lt;/p&gt;</code>
    </pre>

h3 Lists
h4 Base
p.-text Use <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> tags for unordered lists and <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> tags for ordered lists.
.a-grid
  .a-col.-w6
    .example.-mb3
      ul.-text
        li List item 1
        li List item 2
          ul
            li List item 2.1
            li List item 2.2
        li List item 3
        li List item 4
      :code(lang="html")
        <ul class="-text">
          <li></li>
        </ul>
  .a-col.-w6
    .example.-mb3
      ol.-text
        li List item 1
        li List item 2
          ul
            li List item 2.1
            li List item 2.2
        li List item 3
        li List item 4
      :code(lang="html")
        <ol class="-text">
          <li></li>
        </ol>
h4 No style
p.-text To remove default list styling, apply the class <code>.-noStyle</code>
.example.-mb3
  ul.-text.-noStyle.-m3
    li List item 1
    li List item 2
      ul.-noStyle
        li List item 2.1
        li List item 2.2
    li List item 3
    li List item 4
  :code(lang="html")
    <ul class="-text -noStyle">
      <li></li>
    </ul>
h4 Inline
p.-text To display list items inline, apply the class <code>.-inline</code>
.example.-mb3
  ul.-text.-inline.-m3
    li List item 1
    li List item 2
      ul.-inline
        li List item 2.1
        li List item 2.2
    li List item 3
    li List item 4
  :code(lang="html")
    <ul class="-text -inline">
      <li></li>
    </ul>
h3 Blockquotes
p.-text Blockquotes are used to quote content from another source.
.example.-mb3
  blockquote.-m3
    p.-text Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum lacus lacus, dictum quis mauris vel, commodo condimentum odio. Praesent lacus metus, vehicula at orci ac, fringilla mollis mauris.
  :code(lang="html")
    <blockquote>
      <p class="-text">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum lacus lacus, dictum quis mauris vel, commodo condimentum odio. Praesent lacus metus, vehicula at orci ac, fringilla mollis mauris.</p>
    </blockquote>
h3 Text alignment
p.-text Change text alignment to justified, left, center, or right.
.example.-mb3
  .-m3
    p.-text.-textJustify This text will render as justified
    p.-text.-textLeft This text will render as left aligned
    p.-text.-textCenter This text will render as center aligned
    p.-text.-textRight This text will render as right aligned
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-textJustify">This text will render as justified</p>
      <p class="-textLeft">This text will render as left aligned</p>
      <p class="-textCenter">This text will render as center aligned</p>
      <p class="-textRight">This text will render as right aligned</p>
h3 Text transform
p.-text Change text transform to lowercase, uppercase, or capitalized.
.example.-mb3
  .-m3
    p.-text.-textLowercase This text will render as lowercase
    p.-text.-textUppercase This text will render as uppercase
    p.-text.-textCapitalized This text will render as capitalized
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-textLowercase">This text will render as lowercase</p>
      <p class="-textUppercase">This text will render as uppercase</p>
      <p class="-textCapitalized">This text will render as capitalized</p>
h3 Text weight
p.-text Change text weight to thin, normal, bold, or bolder.
.example.-mb3
  .-m3
    p.-text.-textThin This text will render as thin
    p.-text.-textNormal This text will render as normal
    p.-text.-textBold This text will render as bold
    p.-text.-textBolder This text will render as bolder
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-textThin">This text will render as thin</p>
      <p class="-textNormal">This text will render as normal</p>
      <p class="-textBold">This text will render as bold</p>
      <p class="-textBolder">This text will render as bolder</p>
h3 Text wrapping
p.-text Prevent text wrapping with nowrap or control overflow with truncate.
.example.-mb3
  .-m3
    p.-text.-textNoWrap(style="width: 11rem;background:#eeeeee;") This text will render without wrapping
    p.-text.-textTruncate(style="width: 11rem;") This text will truncate with an ellipsis
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-textNoWrap">This text will render without wrapping</p>
      <p class="-textTruncate">This text will truncate with an ellipsis</p>
